info.name: CVEDIA-RT
info.description:
CVEDIA-RT REST API documentation

Before using this collection, make sure you set the `SERVER_URL` variable to the IP and port you're running CVEDIA-RT.

In this example we're setting input to a RTSP stream

item.name: API Instance set state Output RTSP

request.description:
Sets scoped state dictionary from a running instance

In this example CVEDIA-RT will spin it's own RTSP server at port `8554` , listen to all ips and expect connections on path `/test` , so the full URI would look like `rtsp://127.0.0.1:8554/test`

item.name: API Instance set state Output RTMP

request.description:
Sets scoped state dictionary from a running instance

This examples outputs data to an RTMP server, for example RED5, expected to be running at `rtmp://127.0.0.1:1935/live/test`
